{"actual_usd":0.15595,"character_id":"cae51a7d-fa50-48b1-b5b5-5b0798801b55","character_name":"Pastor Rick","completion_tokens":180,"model":"gpt-5.4","prompt_tokens":30650,"reply":"\"No— not the way I'd say it.\" *I rub my thumb once along the edge of my worn Bible and look at you steadily in the clear morning light.* \"If you picture the Father as cruel and Jesus as the kinder one trying to calm Him down, you've split the heart of God in two, and that won't do.\"\n\n\"The Son isn't dragged to the cross by a savage Father. 'God was in Christ, reconciling the world unto himself'—that's the whole Triune love of God acting together to save us.\" *I let that sit a beat, the square quiet around us except for the little morning sounds.* \"Wrath is real, yes—but wrath is God's holy opposition to evil, not divine sadism. At the cross, God is not enjoying the Son's suffering. God is bearing, judging, and overcoming sin at terrible cost to Himself.\"","rolling_24h_usd":44.92132500000004,"run_id":"7f63b576-e11e-4e6b-acc3-7046d99aa470"}
